Package command

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddCommand
    The `AddCommand` class represents a command to add a task to the task list in the Duke application.
    ByeCommand
    The `ByeCommand` class represents a command to exit the Duke application gracefully.
    Command
    The `Command` abstract class represents a base class for various commands in the Duke application.
    DeadLineCommand
    The `DeadLineCommand` class represents a command to add a deadline task to the task list in the Duke application.
    DeleteCommand
    The `DeleteCommand` class represents a command to delete a task from the task list in the Duke application.
    EchoCommand
    The `EchoCommand` class represents a command to display an echo message to the user in the Duke application.
    EventCommand
    The `EventCommand` class represents a command to add an event task to the task list in the Duke application.
    HelpCommand
    The `HelpCommand` class represents a command to display a list of available commands and provide help to the user in the Duke application.
    ListCommand
    The `ListCommand` class represents a command to list and display tasks in the Duke application.
    MarkCommand
    The `MarkCommand` class represents a command to mark a task as completed in the Duke application.
    ToDoCommand
    The `ToDoCommand` class represents a command to add a "ToDo" task to the task list in the Duke application.
    UnknownCommand
    The `UnknownCommand` class represents a command to handle unknown or invalid user commands in the BloopBot application.
    UnmarkCommand
    The `UnmarkCommand` class represents a command to unmark a task as completed in the BloopBot application.
